    question: 'Define identification. Enumerate the data used for identification. Describe age estimation in living subjects and in dead bodies / skeletal remains.',
    answer: `<h4>Definition of Identification</h4>
<p>Identification is the recognition of an individual based on physical, biological, dental, fingerprint, or DNA characteristics. As declared in the Universal Declaration of Human Rights — "Everyone has the right to recognition everywhere as a person before the law."</p>
<h4>Data Used for Identification (16 categories)</h4>
<ol><li>Religion · 2. Race · 3. Sex · 4. Age · 5. Stature</li>
<li>Dactylography (fingerprints) · 7. Footprints · 8. Cheiloscopy (lip prints)</li>
<li>Tattoo marks · 10. Scars · 11. Deformities · 12. Anthropometry</li>
<li>Teeth · 14. DNA typing · 15. Blood group + HLA typing</li>
<li>Miscellaneous — complexion, hair, clothes, personal effects, handwriting, voice, occupation marks, gait, ear morphology, palate prints, frontal sinuses, X-ray</li></ol>
<p>★ Per Interpol DVI: <strong>PRIMARY</strong> identifiers (fingerprint, dental, DNA) alone suffice. <strong>SECONDARY</strong> identifiers (tattoos, scars, personal effects, visual recognition) are supportive only.</p>
<h4>Age Estimation in Living Subjects</h4>
<h5>A. Foetus / Newborn:</h5>
<ul><li><strong>Haase formula</strong>: up to 5 mo, length² = age (mo); after 5 mo, length / 5 = age</li>
<li>Quickening 4 mo IUL · viability 7 mo IUL</li>
<li>Ossification: calcaneum + talus + cuboid + distal femur present in full-term</li></ul>
<h5>B. Children and Adolescents:</h5>
<ul><li><strong>DENTITION</strong> — eruption sequence:<ul>
<li>Primary teeth: lower central incisor 6 mo → 1st molar 1 yr → canine 1.5 yr → 2nd molar 2 yr (half-year rule)</li>
<li>Permanent teeth: 1st molar 6 yr → central incisor 7-8 yr → ... → 3rd molar 17-25 yr</li></ul></li>
<li><strong>OSSIFICATION centres</strong> — appearance + fusion:<ul>
<li>Carpal sequence: Capitate (1-3 mo) → Hamate → Triquetral → Lunate → Trapezium → Trapezoid → Scaphoid (4-7 yr) → PISIFORM (9-12 yr, last)</li>
<li>Long bone fusion: triradiate cartilage 13-16 yr · femur head 14-17 yr · distal radius 17-20 yr · iliac crest 17-20 yr · <strong>medial clavicle 20-22 yr (last)</strong></li></ul></li>
<li><strong>Anthropometry</strong> — height, weight, head circumference (against growth charts)</li>
<li><strong>Tanner staging</strong> (sexual maturity rating, T1-T5) — for 9-18 yr</li></ul>
<h5>C. Adults &gt; 25 years:</h5>
<ul><li><strong>Gustafson\'s method</strong> (teeth) — 6 parameters scored 0-3:
<ol><li>Attrition</li><li>Periodontosis</li><li>Secondary dentine</li><li>Root resorption</li><li>Cementum apposition</li><li>★ Root transparency (single most important)</li></ol></li>
<li><strong>Skeletal changes</strong>: lipping of lumbar vertebrae 40-50 yr · xiphoid-sternum fusion 40 yr · manubrium-body fusion 60 yr · calcification of thyroid / hyoid 40+ yr</li>
<li><strong>Skin / external</strong>: wrinkles · graying · baldness · arcus senilis · presbyopia · cataract</li></ul>
<h4>Age Estimation in Dead Bodies / Skeletal Remains</h4>
<ul><li><strong>All living methods apply</strong> (dentition, ossification, Gustafson) PLUS</li>
<li><strong>Skull sutures</strong>: anterior fontanelle 2 yr · metopic 3-8 yr · sagittal 30-40 yr · coronal 38-50 yr · lambdoid 45-50 yr (variable, ± 5-10 yr accuracy)</li>
<li><strong>Vertebral ring epiphyses</strong> fuse by 25 yr</li>
<li><strong>Sternal end of rib</strong> calcification + shape (Iscan-Loth criteria)</li>
<li><strong>Pubic symphysis</strong> changes (Todd-Brooks-Suchey)</li>
<li><strong>Auricular surface of ilium</strong> (Lovejoy method)</li>
<li><strong>Biochemical / radiographic</strong>: aspartic acid racemisation · pulp-crown ratio</li></ul>
<h4>Combined X-ray Strategy</h4>
<ul><li>0-5 yr — carpal X-ray + dentition</li>
<li>5-15 yr — wrist X-ray + mixed dentition</li>
<li>15-25 yr — wrist + elbow + shoulder + 3rd molar</li>
<li>&gt; 25 yr — Gustafson + skeletal lipping + medial clavicle</li></ul>
<h4>Medicolegal Importance of Age</h4>
<p>Critical legal milestones: &lt; 7 yr no criminal responsibility (IPC 82); 7-12 yr qualified responsibility (IPC 83); 12 yr consent for medical exam; 14 yr factory employment; 18 yr majority + voting + female marriage; 21 yr male marriage; 25 yr assembly candidate; 7 yr unheard-of presumption of death (BSA 110).</p>`,
